    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-28T07:07:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-28T07:07:00-05:00" n="906"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d906">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Lot 55D128: Black Book, Tab 163: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, United Nations Command</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ridgway</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Joint Chiefs of
                            Staff</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-28T21:07:00+09:00">28
                            December 1951—9:07 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>C–60350. For info, <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss> Adv HNC 673.</p>
                <p>“Sub-delegates on item nbr 4 convened 1100, December 28. <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                        >UNC</gloss> continued to press for accounting for the missing <gloss
                        target="#t_POW1">POW</gloss>’s. The only development of possible
                    significance was one sentence in a long statement from General Lee: ‘About all
                    the personnel of the prisoners of war whom we have captured in the past Ave are
                    now putting the data in order and checking the data.’ In view of this the <gloss
                        target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> decided to postpone raising the question of the
                    exchange of civilians under the release and exchange of <gloss target="#t_POW1"
                        >POW</gloss>’s. Recessed at 1345 to reconvene at 1100 tomorrow. Sgd
                    Joy.”</p>
            </div>
        </body>
